<item>
            <title>[SPR-7400] Improve handling of static resources </title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7400</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Building on the newly added ResourceHttpRequestHandler, the following advance features should be re-considered:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Minification should be applied to text-based resources where possible e.g. .js (should be possible to disable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Resource bundling should be supported.  This provides the ability to load multiple resources in one HTTP request, which can improve performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Resource versioning should be supported.  This causes clients to refresh cached resources when a new version of the application is deployed.  This prevents clients from working with stale content after deployment of a new version. (should be possible to disable, when disabled no caching should be performed)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The ability to serve GZip compressed resources should be further expanded to consider disk-cached pre-compressed versions of the resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
